1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:03,670
[Alice] <i>Do they really not</i>
<i>believe that Edong's still alive?</i>

2
00:00:03,753 --> 00:00:05,422
<i>We can share Edong's picture</i>

3
00:00:05,505 --> 00:00:07,632
<i>to get information about his whereabouts.</i>

4
00:00:07,716 --> 00:00:09,175
<i>Edong doesn't have a scar on his back.</i>

5
00:00:11,177 --> 00:00:12,178
<i>It's Kyle…</i>

6
00:00:12,262 --> 00:00:13,596
<i>He was here in Amurao.</i>

7
00:00:13,680 --> 00:00:15,056
<i>- Kyle Sebastian?</i>
<i>- Yes.</i>

8
00:00:15,140 --> 00:00:18,268
<i>He had a good reason</i>
<i>to kill Louisa, remember?</i>

9
00:00:19,060 --> 00:00:20,145
<i>What are you doing?</i>

10
00:00:20,228 --> 00:00:21,604
<i>Let go of me, Kyle!</i>

11
00:00:22,605 --> 00:00:25,150
<i>Why didn't anyone</i>
<i>know they came back here?</i>

12
00:00:25,233 --> 00:00:26,276
<i>No matter what happens, Beth,</i>

13
00:00:26,359 --> 00:00:28,528
<i>even if you become a serial killer,</i>

14
00:00:28,611 --> 00:00:30,113
<i>I'll still love you.</i>

15
00:00:33,825 --> 00:00:38,038
[foreboding music playing]

16
00:00:53,928 --> 00:00:58,224
[foreboding music continues]

17
00:01:04,397 --> 00:01:05,565
[groans]

18
00:01:09,611 --> 00:01:10,820
[grunts]

19
00:01:16,868 --> 00:01:18,161
[exhales heavily]

20
00:01:24,959 --> 00:01:29,339
[music turns unsettling]

21
00:01:33,635 --> 00:01:39,808
[phone buzzing]

22
00:01:40,725 --> 00:01:41,851
Hello?

23
00:01:45,605 --> 00:01:47,148
Any update on Yuri?

24
00:02:01,579 --> 00:02:07,001
[unsettling music continues]

25
00:02:15,635 --> 00:02:17,262
- [man] Okay.
- [clerk] Your room number.

26
00:02:17,345 --> 00:02:19,764
- [girl] Mommy…
- What is it?

27
00:02:19,848 --> 00:02:21,683
- Let's play, Mommy.
- Later. We'll check in first.

28
00:02:21,766 --> 00:02:23,309
- Please.
- Go over there, please.

29
00:02:23,393 --> 00:02:24,978
- You're misbehaving right now.
- [man] Okay. Thank you.

30
00:02:25,061 --> 00:02:28,189
- We're still checking in.
- [clerk] Card or cash payment?

31
00:02:28,273 --> 00:02:29,941
- [man] Cash.
- [clerk] Okay, sir.

32
00:02:30,024 --> 00:02:33,736
[unsettling music continues]

33
00:02:39,659 --> 00:02:44,038
[unsettling music intensifies]

34
00:02:47,959 --> 00:02:53,673
[suspenseful music playing]

35
00:02:58,511 --> 00:03:00,346
[inhales shakily]

36
00:03:07,979 --> 00:03:13,693
[suspenseful music continues]

37
00:03:17,113 --> 00:03:18,448
[girl] Mommy…

38
00:03:18,531 --> 00:03:20,909
[man] What happened to our daughter?

39
00:03:21,534 --> 00:03:23,036
- [man] I know.
- [girl] Mommy…

40
00:03:23,119 --> 00:03:28,291
[suspenseful music continues]

41
00:03:36,841 --> 00:03:43,473
[theme music playing]

42
00:04:55,003 --> 00:04:56,462
[man] Why are you asking that?

43
00:04:56,546 --> 00:04:58,965
We're just trying
to clarify what happened.

44
00:05:00,925 --> 00:05:02,093
[man] Clarify?

45
00:05:02,969 --> 00:05:06,180
Or are you trying
to pin Louisa's death on Kyle?

46
00:05:06,264 --> 00:05:07,765
That's not what we're saying.

47
00:05:07,849 --> 00:05:09,225
We're investigating.

48
00:05:10,101 --> 00:05:12,270
And if your friend
has nothing to do with it,

49
00:05:12,353 --> 00:05:13,730
then you have nothing to worry about.

50
00:05:13,813 --> 00:05:14,689
[scoffs]

51
00:05:15,231 --> 00:05:16,274
Who's scared?

52
00:05:16,649 --> 00:05:19,652
Someone was already
locked up for Louisa's death.

53
00:05:19,736 --> 00:05:22,989
Exactly. So can
you just answer the questions?

54
00:05:24,115 --> 00:05:27,577
[tense music playing]

55
00:05:27,660 --> 00:05:30,371
Yes, he was here in Amurao back then,

56
00:05:30,747 --> 00:05:34,083
but only me and one other friend knew.

57
00:05:34,584 --> 00:05:37,003
Were you together
the night Louisa was killed?

58
00:05:37,545 --> 00:05:38,546
[Erica] Why did he come home?

59
00:05:39,088 --> 00:05:40,214
What was he doing here?

60
00:05:41,799 --> 00:05:43,843
[Myrna] I don't like where this is going.

61
00:05:44,761 --> 00:05:47,722
That's why we're
asking you, Mrs. Sebastian.

62
00:05:47,805 --> 00:05:50,016
- [music fades]
- We know you can tell us something,

63
00:05:50,600 --> 00:05:52,435
so we can clear up the misunderstanding

64
00:05:52,518 --> 00:05:54,604
about why Kyle was here.

65
00:05:54,687 --> 00:05:57,106
He never went near your friend again,

66
00:05:57,190 --> 00:05:59,442
especially after what she did to him?

67
00:05:59,525 --> 00:06:03,237
We don't even live in
Amurao anymore. We live in the US.

68
00:06:03,321 --> 00:06:06,199
My son had nothing
to do with what happened,

69
00:06:06,282 --> 00:06:09,160
especially not with that woman's death!

70
00:06:09,786 --> 00:06:11,662
I can't believe you, Edward,

71
00:06:11,746 --> 00:06:15,625
you let her ruin my vacation for this?

72
00:06:15,708 --> 00:06:16,918
How rude!

73
00:06:17,460 --> 00:06:20,797
Myrna, isn't it better
that my niece asks you directly

74
00:06:20,880 --> 00:06:24,425
than letting other gossipers do it?

75
00:06:25,051 --> 00:06:26,844
I also don't want people asking around

76
00:06:26,928 --> 00:06:29,806
and then you find out the
rumors being spread about your son.

77
00:06:29,889 --> 00:06:30,723
[huffs]

78
00:06:31,557 --> 00:06:34,727
Mrs. Sebastian,
what does Kyle do in the US?

79
00:06:36,104 --> 00:06:40,566
He runs our restaurants there.

80
00:06:40,650 --> 00:06:45,029
He's married,
with kids, and perfectly happy.

81
00:06:45,446 --> 00:06:49,283
He's successful
despite what you did to him.

82
00:06:50,243 --> 00:06:52,495
And you and your friends?

83
00:06:54,372 --> 00:06:58,668
Well, if that's
your definition of happiness, then…

84
00:06:59,168 --> 00:07:02,130
Yes, I live in the US too.

85
00:07:02,213 --> 00:07:04,340
I'm an accounting manager for

86
00:07:04,423 --> 00:07:06,968
Walton-Page Business Consultants
based in LA.

87
00:07:07,051 --> 00:07:08,010
Maybe you've heard of it?

88
00:07:09,053 --> 00:07:11,973
Oh, and I'm married and we have a son.

89
00:07:12,056 --> 00:07:14,600
My husband, Scott Miller,

90
00:07:14,684 --> 00:07:17,395
is actually the CEO of Global Innovatives,

91
00:07:17,478 --> 00:07:20,857
a green company
that deals with sustainable energy.

92
00:07:21,607 --> 00:07:27,780
I heard Kyle came back here
because he messed up in the US?

93
00:07:27,864 --> 00:07:29,282
[tense music resumes]

94
00:07:29,365 --> 00:07:32,410
I honestly don't remember.
That was so long ago.

95
00:07:33,035 --> 00:07:36,831
All I remember is we met a few times,

96
00:07:37,290 --> 00:07:39,917
then they went back to the States.

97
00:07:41,043 --> 00:07:45,840
Yes, he was angry at Louisa, but kill her?

98
00:07:46,591 --> 00:07:48,050
Do you really think he'd
fly back to the Philippines

99
00:07:48,134 --> 00:07:50,219
for your crazy friend?

100
00:07:50,803 --> 00:07:53,681
Come on! Think about it!

101
00:07:54,140 --> 00:07:56,267
[Erica] You made up stories
and painted her as a villain.

102
00:07:56,350 --> 00:07:58,895
I could sue you for grave slander.

103
00:08:00,271 --> 00:08:02,482
Or are you still doing that now?

104
00:08:03,858 --> 00:08:06,944
So if I were you,
I'd be careful with what I say.

105
00:08:07,028 --> 00:08:09,113
[music intensifies, fades]

106
00:08:09,197 --> 00:08:10,656
[Myrna] That's not true!

107
00:08:10,740 --> 00:08:13,242
We came home for a vacation.

108
00:08:13,784 --> 00:08:15,620
I don't know what you think you know.

109
00:08:15,953 --> 00:08:17,371
That's all fake news!

110
00:08:17,788 --> 00:08:22,168
If your lies spread,
I'll report all of you to the police.

111
00:08:23,586 --> 00:08:26,672
And you, I'll tell Father about this.

112
00:08:27,924 --> 00:08:29,509
[gate creaks, closes]

113
00:08:29,592 --> 00:08:32,637
[reflective music playing]

114
00:08:32,720 --> 00:08:36,015
- [breathes softly]
- [inhales sharply]

115
00:08:36,098 --> 00:08:37,517
[Erica] Same here.

116
00:08:38,142 --> 00:08:40,853
We didn't get any
information that actually helps us.

117
00:08:43,481 --> 00:08:45,525
Okay, thanks, Alice. I'll see you later.

118
00:08:48,319 --> 00:08:49,195
[tsk]

119
00:08:54,450 --> 00:08:55,743
So what do we do now?

120
00:08:57,328 --> 00:08:59,705
Alice said Kyle's mom was defensive,

121
00:09:00,248 --> 00:09:01,415
which was expected.

122
00:09:01,999 --> 00:09:06,212
But she confirmed Kyle was
in Amurao the week Louisa died.

123
00:09:06,837 --> 00:09:08,381
[Marco inhales deeply]

124
00:09:08,756 --> 00:09:10,716
Let's talk to Kyle's other friend.

125
00:09:11,342 --> 00:09:12,885
Maybe we'll learn something.

126
00:09:13,344 --> 00:09:16,264
That'll be hard. His loyalty is with Kyle.

127
00:09:17,723 --> 00:09:22,228
[uneasy music playing]

128
00:09:35,616 --> 00:09:40,037
[music becomes melancholic]

129
00:09:45,001 --> 00:09:47,086
- Have some coffee first.
- [music fades]

130
00:09:47,878 --> 00:09:52,425
Sorry, Uncle.
I really can't stand that woman.

131
00:09:52,508 --> 00:09:54,260
[Althea murmurs, chuckles]
Yeah, like that.

132
00:09:55,636 --> 00:09:57,597
Ever since we were kids,

133
00:09:57,680 --> 00:10:00,057
the way she treated Louisa…

134
00:10:00,391 --> 00:10:03,269
It seems like she never changed.

135
00:10:03,352 --> 00:10:05,062
[chuckles] Oh, Alice.

136
00:10:06,063 --> 00:10:07,523
That's just how Myrna is.

137
00:10:08,274 --> 00:10:09,567
I've gotten used to it.

138
00:10:11,068 --> 00:10:11,944
Wow.

139
00:10:13,237 --> 00:10:16,991
Honestly, your patience is amazing, Uncle.

140
00:10:17,700 --> 00:10:21,037
No wonder the church trusts you so much.

141
00:10:21,120 --> 00:10:22,705
You're kind to everyone.

142
00:10:22,788 --> 00:10:24,248
[chuckles]

143
00:10:24,332 --> 00:10:28,628
I try. It's hard sometimes but,

144
00:10:29,629 --> 00:10:31,047
I still try.

145
00:10:34,300 --> 00:10:35,801
Hey, are you ready to go?

146
00:10:35,885 --> 00:10:37,470
Oh, yeah.

147
00:10:39,305 --> 00:10:42,975
Uncle, thank
you again for babysitting Seth.

148
00:10:44,977 --> 00:10:48,773
I canceled my therapy session yesterday,
so I really can't skip today.

149
00:10:51,108 --> 00:10:57,323
[pensive music playing]

150
00:10:58,991 --> 00:11:00,868
Althea, thank you too.

151
00:11:01,243 --> 00:11:02,912
It's nothing, Alice.

152
00:11:02,995 --> 00:11:06,791
I love taking care of Seth. He's so sweet.

153
00:11:06,874 --> 00:11:08,459
[Edward chuckles]

154
00:11:10,836 --> 00:11:15,800
You know, when you smile,
you really look like Erica.

155
00:11:17,593 --> 00:11:18,594
Really?

156
00:11:18,677 --> 00:11:22,973
[melancholic music playing]

157
00:11:23,057 --> 00:11:26,769
But Erica doesn't smile much.

158
00:11:30,898 --> 00:11:36,695
Um… I think my family
has something to do with that.

159
00:11:40,825 --> 00:11:42,034
- Okay.
- [music fades]

160
00:11:49,583 --> 00:11:50,584
Uh…

161
00:11:52,670 --> 00:11:54,213
- [Mel] Hi.
- Hi, Mel.

162
00:11:56,173 --> 00:11:58,551
- Where's Reema?
- She can't make it.

163
00:12:00,469 --> 00:12:02,638
But I told her I needed to talk to her.

164
00:12:02,721 --> 00:12:05,683
Look, Mel,
Reema sent me here to tell you…

165
00:12:06,183 --> 00:12:08,227
The owners want to suspend

166
00:12:08,310 --> 00:12:10,771
the Grace and Glam campaign with you.

167
00:12:10,855 --> 00:12:14,316
[ominous music playing]

168
00:12:14,400 --> 00:12:15,943
Oh… What?

169
00:12:18,112 --> 00:12:20,197
But our contract…
it's good for a year, right?

170
00:12:20,281 --> 00:12:23,492
Yes, Mel, but because of the scandal…

171
00:12:23,576 --> 00:12:25,077
Anton's scandal.

172
00:12:26,579 --> 00:12:28,622
I shouldn't be the one paying for that.

173
00:12:28,706 --> 00:12:30,749
Mel, I'm really sorry.

174
00:12:31,500 --> 00:12:33,544
Why didn't Reema face me herself?

175
00:12:33,627 --> 00:12:35,421
Why can't she tell me this herself?

176
00:12:36,505 --> 00:12:38,299
You know what? I'll just call her.

177
00:12:38,382 --> 00:12:39,800
Mel, please.

178
00:12:42,803 --> 00:12:44,555
[line ringing]

179
00:12:45,431 --> 00:12:46,557
Yes, Mel?

180
00:12:47,224 --> 00:12:48,601
Reema, I needed to talk to you

181
00:12:48,684 --> 00:12:50,853
because I wanted
to update my photos for the brand.

182
00:12:51,228 --> 00:12:52,980
I really needed the boost.

183
00:12:53,689 --> 00:12:55,399
<i>And I wanted people to see</i>

184
00:12:55,483 --> 00:12:57,902
that Grace and Glam still supports me.

185
00:12:58,360 --> 00:13:01,947
And then I'm finding out right now,
that you're cutting me off?

186
00:13:02,990 --> 00:13:04,283
No, dear.

187
00:13:04,366 --> 00:13:10,706
<i>You know the owners of G</i>
<i>and G are close to the Montenegros.</i>

188
00:13:10,789 --> 00:13:12,958
Yeah, I know, but when the rumors came out

189
00:13:13,042 --> 00:13:14,543
that I was an abusive wife,

190
00:13:14,627 --> 00:13:17,630
you still fought for
me as your endorser, so…

191
00:13:17,713 --> 00:13:19,798
Why now? What changed?

192
00:13:19,882 --> 00:13:22,593
I'm still fighting for you.

193
00:13:22,676 --> 00:13:25,346
But they're dead set, Mel.

194
00:13:26,472 --> 00:13:28,182
<i>There's nothing I can do.</i>

195
00:13:28,599 --> 00:13:29,975
I'm so sorry.

196
00:13:31,769 --> 00:13:33,646
[clicks tongue, exhales shakily]

197
00:13:36,607 --> 00:13:37,816
I'm sorry.

198
00:13:42,696 --> 00:13:46,909
[ominous music continues, fades]

199
00:13:47,785 --> 00:13:54,124
[pensive music playing]

200
00:14:12,977 --> 00:14:14,478
[music fades]

201
00:14:14,562 --> 00:14:15,479
Chloe.

202
00:14:15,563 --> 00:14:17,231
Why are you alone?

203
00:14:18,482 --> 00:14:20,109
Where's your twin?

204
00:14:22,945 --> 00:14:24,488
Aren't you going home yet?

205
00:14:24,572 --> 00:14:27,199
We still have a meeting.
You guys go ahead.

206
00:14:32,872 --> 00:14:36,584
You wanted to be
a journalist when you were young, right?

207
00:14:37,835 --> 00:14:39,003
[chuckles softly]

208
00:14:39,086 --> 00:14:40,087
Yes.

209
00:14:43,215 --> 00:14:44,174
Why…

210
00:14:44,758 --> 00:14:46,302
Why didn't you?

211
00:14:48,012 --> 00:14:48,971
Uh…

212
00:14:49,054 --> 00:14:51,974
A lot has happened.

213
00:14:52,057 --> 00:14:54,560
I wanted to focus more on our family.

214
00:14:55,185 --> 00:14:56,103
[Chloe] But…

215
00:14:56,186 --> 00:14:58,772
Journalists can do
their jobs while raising a family.

216
00:14:58,856 --> 00:15:02,526
[pensive music continues]

217
00:15:02,610 --> 00:15:03,485
Yes.

218
00:15:04,403 --> 00:15:07,072
But… But I don't want
to be a journalist anymore.

219
00:15:07,156 --> 00:15:09,283
I prefer being a teacher.

220
00:15:18,626 --> 00:15:21,921
You're telling the truth, right, Ma?

221
00:15:22,546 --> 00:15:27,468
[pensive music continues]

222
00:15:31,764 --> 00:15:35,309
[man] Ryan and Erica even ganged up on me.

223
00:15:35,392 --> 00:15:38,270
[music becomes unsettling]

224
00:15:38,354 --> 00:15:39,521
Just a sec, dear.

225
00:15:48,322 --> 00:15:52,576
[unsettling music continues]

226
00:15:53,953 --> 00:15:56,997
[reporter] <i>So, how does it feel</i>
<i>to be the new face of Grace & Glam?</i>

227
00:15:57,081 --> 00:16:00,250
<i>Well, Grace & Glam's been my favorite</i>
<i>since I was a teenager.</i>

228
00:16:01,043 --> 00:16:03,045
<i>I've been using this brand for years and,</i>

229
00:16:03,128 --> 00:16:05,005
<i>even when I thought</i>
<i>I was going to be a doctor.</i>

230
00:16:05,089 --> 00:16:08,050
<i>I used to style myself using their pieces,</i>

231
00:16:08,133 --> 00:16:10,928
<i>and that's actually what kickstarted</i>

232
00:16:11,011 --> 00:16:13,847
<i>and inspired me to pursue my styling.</i>

233
00:16:13,931 --> 00:16:16,058
<i>So, this brand has really been a part</i>

234
00:16:16,141 --> 00:16:18,477
<i>of my journey in</i>
<i>fashion for the longest time.</i>

235
00:16:19,853 --> 00:16:21,230
[phone buzzing]

236
00:16:21,313 --> 00:16:22,231
[breathes sharply]

237
00:16:22,314 --> 00:16:25,693
[buzzing continues]

238
00:16:27,820 --> 00:16:31,740
[unsettling music continues]

239
00:16:31,824 --> 00:16:32,908
I told you,

240
00:16:33,617 --> 00:16:34,994
you'd lose Grace & Glam.

241
00:16:36,787 --> 00:16:38,372
And you lost your show.

242
00:16:39,498 --> 00:16:40,666
I'll get it back.

243
00:16:41,166 --> 00:16:42,042
As for you,

244
00:16:43,002 --> 00:16:44,044
<i>on the other hand,</i>

245
00:16:44,503 --> 00:16:46,922
I'll make sure you'll
never recover from this.

246
00:16:47,006 --> 00:16:50,300
[unsettling music continues]

247
00:16:50,384 --> 00:16:51,802
When I'm done…

248
00:16:53,137 --> 00:16:54,596
you'll have nothing left.

249
00:16:56,557 --> 00:17:01,729
[unsettling music intensifies]

250
00:17:03,105 --> 00:17:04,606
[breathes shakily]

251
00:17:04,690 --> 00:17:05,607
No.

252
00:17:05,691 --> 00:17:07,526
[breathes shakily]

253
00:17:07,609 --> 00:17:08,986
Don't panic, Mel.

254
00:17:10,696 --> 00:17:12,364
You're not going to lose everything.

255
00:17:14,283 --> 00:17:15,784
[sobs]

256
00:17:15,868 --> 00:17:17,578
You won't lose, Mel.

257
00:17:18,996 --> 00:17:21,623
[sobs] You can't lose.

258
00:17:23,792 --> 00:17:26,420
[unsettling music continues]

259
00:17:26,503 --> 00:17:28,422
[Tim] <i>If you publicize those videos,</i>

260
00:17:29,173 --> 00:17:32,009
<i>you'll have clear</i>
<i>proof that you're not lying.</i>

261
00:17:33,886 --> 00:17:36,472
<i>That will shut up the haters.</i>

262
00:17:39,683 --> 00:17:40,934
- Yes, dude.
- [music fades]

263
00:17:41,018 --> 00:17:43,187
She's so arrogant now
that she has become a lawyer.

264
00:17:43,812 --> 00:17:45,230
But I didn't say anything.

265
00:17:45,647 --> 00:17:46,940
Yes, I swear.

266
00:17:47,316 --> 00:17:48,942
I mean, it took 14 years

267
00:17:49,026 --> 00:17:51,570
before they found out
that Kyle came back to Amurao.

268
00:17:51,653 --> 00:17:53,030
[uneasy music playing]

269
00:17:53,113 --> 00:17:55,574
[man] I know how to keep secrets.

270
00:17:55,657 --> 00:17:58,285
You better make sure to do the same.

271
00:17:58,368 --> 00:17:59,661
Be careful.

272
00:17:59,745 --> 00:18:02,164
They might be on their way to you now.

273
00:18:03,624 --> 00:18:07,753
[uneasy music continues]

274
00:18:10,255 --> 00:18:11,715
[music fades]

275
00:18:11,799 --> 00:18:13,592
[sighs heavily] Mama said…

276
00:18:15,969 --> 00:18:17,971
she doesn't want
to become a journalist anymore.

277
00:18:20,849 --> 00:18:24,853
And that she prefers being a teacher.

278
00:18:27,189 --> 00:18:28,273
[sighs heavily]

279
00:18:28,357 --> 00:18:29,358
But…

280
00:18:31,401 --> 00:18:33,278
When I asked her if it was true…

281
00:18:36,073 --> 00:18:37,074
she didn't answer.

282
00:18:44,123 --> 00:18:45,749
[breathes sharply]

283
00:18:46,708 --> 00:18:47,709
What if…

284
00:18:49,253 --> 00:18:51,046
Papa was right?

285
00:18:51,130 --> 00:18:55,926
[somber music playing]

286
00:18:56,009 --> 00:18:58,762
What if Mama isn't happy with us?

287
00:19:02,391 --> 00:19:03,475
[inhales sharply]

288
00:19:03,976 --> 00:19:06,353
What if it's true that Mama hates me?

289
00:19:08,605 --> 00:19:10,482
What if I destroyed her dream?

290
00:19:12,568 --> 00:19:14,653
I know that having
me wasn't in their plan.

291
00:19:14,736 --> 00:19:16,947
[sobs, sniffles]

292
00:19:17,030 --> 00:19:20,409
Mama got pregnant
before she graduated from college

293
00:19:20,492 --> 00:19:22,369
that's why she didn't become a journalist.

294
00:19:22,870 --> 00:19:24,913
They didn't keep that from me.

295
00:19:25,747 --> 00:19:29,543
I thought Mama was happy despite that.

296
00:19:30,460 --> 00:19:31,545
Oh come on, Chloe.

297
00:19:32,045 --> 00:19:33,797
I'm sure Miss Beth is happy.

298
00:19:34,464 --> 00:19:38,010
But let's say Miss Beth is unhappy.
Why would she blame you?

299
00:19:38,427 --> 00:19:39,428
But still…

300
00:19:41,221 --> 00:19:42,723
Are you serious?

301
00:19:42,806 --> 00:19:44,474
You're really scared?

302
00:19:45,184 --> 00:19:47,519
They never fought like that.

303
00:19:47,603 --> 00:19:49,354
They rarely fight.

304
00:19:49,438 --> 00:19:51,899
[somber music continues]

305
00:19:51,982 --> 00:19:53,275
What if they don't make up…

306
00:19:54,735 --> 00:19:56,486
and choose to break up?

307
00:19:59,907 --> 00:20:01,158
Bruh…

308
00:20:01,241 --> 00:20:02,659
It's okay. Don't cry.

309
00:20:03,410 --> 00:20:04,453
They'll make up.

310
00:20:05,412 --> 00:20:06,330
[sniffles]

311
00:20:06,413 --> 00:20:10,959
[somber music continues]

312
00:20:12,502 --> 00:20:18,342
[crying]

313
00:20:19,635 --> 00:20:25,140
- [line ringing]
- "LOVE."

314
00:20:25,224 --> 00:20:28,852
[uneasy music playing]

315
00:20:36,944 --> 00:20:39,029
[keypad clacking]

316
00:20:39,112 --> 00:20:41,823
"LOVE, PLEASE CALL ME.
I HAVE SOMETHING TO TELL YOU. URGENT."

317
00:20:44,952 --> 00:20:48,622
[uneasy music continues, fades]

318
00:20:50,207 --> 00:20:51,625
[Chloe sniffles] Eww! Cringe!

319
00:20:52,042 --> 00:20:53,460
You started it.

320
00:20:55,837 --> 00:20:56,838
But honestly…

321
00:20:58,632 --> 00:21:00,842
I don't mind you acting all cringe.

322
00:21:01,635 --> 00:21:03,470
I mean, I went on full cringe mode

323
00:21:03,553 --> 00:21:05,764
when I thought my
parents were going to break up.

324
00:21:06,181 --> 00:21:08,016
But they didn't end their marriage.

325
00:21:08,433 --> 00:21:10,394
Yes, and your parents
won't break up either.

326
00:21:12,145 --> 00:21:14,356
No annulment vibes. I promise.

327
00:21:14,439 --> 00:21:18,944
[light-hearted music playing]

328
00:21:22,447 --> 00:21:23,532
Thanks, bro.

329
00:21:24,825 --> 00:21:26,493
I'll go inside now

330
00:21:26,576 --> 00:21:29,746
before your Cringe Master
crown gets passed on to me.

331
00:21:29,830 --> 00:21:34,543
[light-hearted music continues]

332
00:21:39,464 --> 00:21:41,049
[hen clucking]

333
00:21:44,678 --> 00:21:46,138
- [bag zips open]
- [music fades]

334
00:21:48,557 --> 00:21:52,602
[keys jangling]

335
00:21:52,686 --> 00:21:54,271
[doorknob clicks]

336
00:21:55,230 --> 00:21:58,567
[eerie music playing]

337
00:21:58,650 --> 00:21:59,526
Pa?

338
00:22:05,282 --> 00:22:06,533
I'm home.

339
00:22:12,331 --> 00:22:17,961
[eerie music continues]

340
00:22:32,601 --> 00:22:33,685
[phone chimes]

341
00:22:36,146 --> 00:22:40,108
"1 MESSAGE RECEIVED."

342
00:22:50,035 --> 00:22:56,083
[eerie music continues]

343
00:23:13,141 --> 00:23:17,312
[music becomes sinister]

344
00:23:22,609 --> 00:23:24,820
[Edong cackling]

345
00:23:29,825 --> 00:23:34,079
[sinister music crescendos]

346
00:23:35,205 --> 00:23:37,874
<i>I will punish those who sin</i>

347
00:23:37,958 --> 00:23:40,210
<i>including their children</i>

348
00:23:40,293 --> 00:23:43,046
<i>up to the third and fourth generations.</i>

349
00:23:43,130 --> 00:23:44,047
<i>Aah!</i>

350
00:23:44,131 --> 00:23:45,632
[knocking]

351
00:23:45,715 --> 00:23:46,842
<i>Bunny!</i>

352
00:23:46,925 --> 00:23:47,926
<i>Hello!</i>

353
00:23:48,009 --> 00:23:48,885
<i>Seth?</i>

354
00:23:48,969 --> 00:23:50,220
- [Seth] <i>No, don't!</i>
- [Althea grunts]

355
00:23:50,303 --> 00:23:51,805
<i>Let me go!</i>

356
00:23:52,889 --> 00:23:55,433
<i>He's the beloved son of his mother.</i>

357
00:23:55,517 --> 00:23:59,479
<i>The sin of his mother, is also his sin.</i>

358
00:24:00,856 --> 00:24:02,566
[both grunting]
